			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most Useful Bard AA Abilities<a name="39548"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 12 04 7:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just wanted to mention that you're confusing the phrase &quot;damage mitigation&quot; with damage avoidance.
<br />

<br />
mit&#183;i&#183;gate 
<br />
To moderate (a quality or condition) in force or intensity; alleviate.
<br />

<br />
Damage mitigation decreases the total damage you take per hit. Say you have 0% mitigation and are fighting a mob that hits for max 100. When he hits for max, you get hit for 100. If you come back and fight the same mob and you now have 20% mitigation and he hits for max, you only get hit for 80. AAs on this list that affect DAMAGE MITIGATION are: Combat Stability, Innate Defense, and Physical Enhancement.
<br />

<br />
Damage avoidance is the chance to avoid damage entirely by means of dodge, parry, riposte, or general agility (&quot;...but misses!&quot;). AAs on this list that affect DAMAGE AVOIDANCE are: Combat Agility, Lightning Reflexes, and Physical Enhancement.
<br />

<br />
Also, I'm not sure if it's fair to say that CA and LR are better than CS and ID. It's personal preference if you ask me. You'll just notice &quot;but YOU dodge!&quot; a lot more than you would &quot;hit YOU for 470&quot; (rather than &quot;hit YOU for 570&quot;).
<br />

<br />
----
<br />

<br />
Also, if you're going to include Mental Clarity, I think you should also include B&amp;MR -- the AA/point ratio is better than MC (MC comes out to 4 AA per 1 mana/tick, where B&amp;MR is 2.5 AA for 1 mana/tick). Lastly, /rude SCE &amp; Master of the Past.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
