				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most Useful Bard AA Abilities<a name="39646"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 12 04 2:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mitigation does NOT work like it is described above.  The poster suggested that mitigation lowers the maximum hit.  This is absolutely not the case.  Mitigation lowers the AVERAGE damage taken per hit.  So if a mob hits for 100 max as in the example, and you have 20% mitigation, you will STILL get hit for 100 sometimes, but you will take 20% less damage overall, which means you will get hit for full less often as well.
<br />

<br />
Bit don't get sucked into theinking Combat Stability and Innate Defense will lower the max hit of mobs you fight.  They do NOT do that.  They just lower the average damage you take over the long run.  Mobs in hard LDON still hit for 992 many times, even after getting CS3 and ID2.  Just maybe a bit less often.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
