				<td colspan="2"><span>Very nice thread. Thanks to everyone who has contributed to it for the valuable info.
<br />

<br />
I will disagree with the original post on one particular ability, however. 
<br />
I put LR5 as a pretty high priority, mainly because I do a LOT of pulling in groups. When pulling in areas like hard LDoN, you need to do whatever you can to avoid taking damage. It makes a pretty noticable difference.
<br />
I don't have specific parsing logs or anything, but I can attest that it helps to get spammed with misses rather than taking a stun and getting beat up in the middle of a pull.
<br />
I pull quick chains, and most of the time I reach the group with my mob before they're done with the last one... if a mez gets resisted, I'm tanking for at least a round. I'll take any damage mitigation I can get prior to putting anything into offensive melee abilities.</span></td>
