				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most Useful Bard AA Abilities<a name="45414"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 10 04 9:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Was looking up earlier at the discussion about damage mitgation.
<br />
it does &gt;NOT&lt; reduce taken damage by a set percent, instead, it raises the percent that you will take reduced damage. So choosing between CA3 and CS3, 10% each, CA is better, no argument. 
<br />
EQ's damage system first compares you and your targets level, attack, and defense, then factors that into a random number, which decides if you're hit, then checks for abilities such as LR/CA, and rolls a random number to see if that removes the hit. Then, AC and attack are factored again into a random number to decide damage. Afterwards, a random number is rolled based on your ID skill, and if so, it reduces the damage from the hit a significant amount.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td height="2"></td>
			</tr><tr>
