				<td colspan="2"><span>My first 12 archetype points were spent on Combat Fury.  I take a slightly different approach from some of the folks around here, and go by this philosophy:  I'm a bard first, a rogue second, and a tank third.  Hence, since I had no song enhancers without 12 archetype points, I put them all into a DPS AA.  I've given my DPS in general a bit more attention than do many bards; my weapons and their proc augs reflect this.  As a late-50's to early-60's bard, I spent a lot of time doing DPS duty, and while our melee is sub-par, it is not inconsequential.  
<br />

<br />
I've since gotten IM3, SM2, and some tanking AA's, but I've also gotten HA5, and am considering grabbing ambidexterity.  While some may think our DPS is crap, it can make a real difference.</span></td>
